						<p>Oh, brilliant! You have excellent voice, and the pitch is indeed perfect. I love it when it turns sinister at the end &#8211; touch of the Mitchell and Webb look there with the curfew? Very nice. On second reading, picked up even more little references to things being wrong (blue sheen&#8230;. just like an egg!). </p>
<p>It may work even better with slightly shorter sentences (breaking up long explanations of how the product product works into more exclamatory ones: Put it in you mouth! Wait for it! .. etc. I think that would sound more natural for a salespitch but it is definitely a  matter of personal preference. </p>
<p>Loved the story, awesome.</p>
